The People of the State of Illinois, Defendant in Error, v. Ed. Carbine, Plaintiff in Error. The People of the State of Illinois, Defendant in Error, v. G. H. Swappach, Plaintiff in Error.Gen. No. 19,255.

(Not to he reported in full.)

Gen. No. 19,256.

(Not to he reported in full.)

Error to the Municipal Court of Chicago; the Hon. Charles- N. Goodnow, Judge, presiding.Heard in the Branch Appellate Court at the October term, 1913.Reversed and remanded.Opinion filed February 4, 1914.

Statement of the Case.

These causes were consolidated for hearing with the case of People v. Crilly, ante, p. 160, and involve precisely the same questions. The decision rendered in that case held controlling.

John D. Farrell, for plaintiffs in error; II. A. Weld, of counsel.Maclay Hoyne, for defendant in error; Francis E. Hinckley and Edward E. Wilson, of counsel. Mr. Justice Baume

delivered the opinion of the court.
